President Obama has announced his intention to nominate and appoint several individuals to key administration posts. The nominees include Brad Carson for General Counsel of the Army, Alastair Fitzpayne for Assistant Secretary for Legislative Affairs at the Department of the Treasury, Michael A. McFaul for Ambassador to the Russian Federation at the Department of State, and Kevin A. Ohlson for Judge at the United States Court of Appeals for the Armed Forces. The appointees include H. Fisk Johnson as a member of the Advisory Committee for Trade Policy and Negotiations, and Thomas L. McKiernan as a member of the Board of Visitors to the United States Air Force Academy. President Obama expressed his pleasure at having these experienced individuals join his administration.